soot.toDex.instructions

Class Insn12x

  • java.lang.Object
    • soot.toDex.instructions.AbstractInsn
      • soot.toDex.instructions.Insn12x
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable, Insn, OneRegInsn, TwoRegInsn

    public class Insn12x
extends AbstractInsn
implements TwoRegInsn
    The "12x" instruction format: It needs one 16-bit code unit, has two registers and is used for general purposes (hence the "x").

    It is used e.g. by the opcodes "move-object", "array-length", the unary operations and the "/2addr" binary operations.
